---
description: MVP scope and complexity limits
alwaysApply: true
---

This project is an MVP for a demo. Prefer working product behavior and clear
team boundaries over production-only complexity.

Allowed by default:

- lowdb JSON storage;
- local/network access without auth;
- manual baseline checks;
- local llama.cpp server;
- simple fallbacks when external services are unavailable;
- best-effort DeckLink compatibility;
- pragmatic TypeScript and Zod validation.

Do not add unless Karen explicitly asks:

- authentication;
- users/roles/permissions;
- complex database replacement;
- migrations framework;
- Kubernetes or deployment platform;
- large Docker orchestration;
- broad dependency upgrades;
- observability stack;
- background job platform;
- multi-tenant architecture;
- large rewrites unrelated to the requested task.

When choosing between two valid approaches:

- pick the smaller MVP-safe change;
- preserve current behavior;
- document intentional behavior changes;
- avoid abstractions that do not remove real complexity.
